OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FOfcom urged to help end    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fbroadband loyalty penalty  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Telecoms regulator Ofcom has been urged
OL,6, to do more to help broadband and mobile
OL,7, customers who pay a "loyalty penalty"  
OL,8, for staying with their provider.       
OL,10,FSome long-standing customers pay more  
OL,11,Fthan new customers for the same service
OL,12,Fand Citizens Advice wants action taken.
OL,14,FIn 2021, Ofcom estimated switching     
OL,15,Fcould save people #83 a year on mobile 
OL,16,Fbills and #61 on broadband.            
OL,18,FA Citizens Advice survey of 3,087 UK   
OL,19,Fpeople suggested up to one-in-seven may
OL,20,Fbe paying a "loyalty penalty".         
